{
  "text": "Suppose we want to make inference about an unknown parameter of interest, say , which has common interpretation across all models. A direct application of the law of total probabilities (see [CITATION_1] for a proof) implies that the posterior distribution of given D is the weighted posterior distribution of that quantity under each model",
